\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {9}{\ignorespaces Correlation transfer from model parameter to behavioral indicators for DMC simulations. Each panel plots generating parameter correlations (x-axis) against observed cross-task indicator correlations (y-axis) for RT difference scores (orange) and accuracy difference scores (blue). Top row: single-parameter correlations (only the named parameter is correlated across tasks; all others remain uncorrelated). Bottom row: multi-parameter correlations (two parameters simultaneously correlated). The dashed identity line marks perfect transfer. Points consistently fall below this line, indicating that even strong parameter-level correlations transfer only partially to indicator-level correlations.}}{29}{figure.caption.24}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {10}{\ignorespaces Correlation transfer from model parameter to behavioral indicators for SSP simulation. As with DMC, each panel plots generating parameter correlations against observed cross-task indicator correlations for RT difference scores (orange) and accuracy difference scores (blue). Single-parameter panels show only the named parameter correlated across tasks. The same attenuation pattern emerges, demonstrating that correlation transfer failure generalizes across model architectures.}}{31}{figure.caption.25}\protected@file@percent }
